Chou's compositions are loosely categorized as pop music. While many of his works fall into contemporary R&B, rap music rap, and rock music rock genres, the term Chou Style zh-tsp t= s= p=zhu sh fnggzh icon cite news  url=http://newsserver.ccwb.net/html1/2006/10/11/f110918.shtml  title=Still Fantasy Two million albums sold recognized for Jay Chou   publisher=www.ccwb.net   date=2006-10-11   accessdate = 2007-06-02 zh icon cite news  url= http://finance.eastday.com/eastday/enjoy/node58771/node58900/node58903/node143675/u1a2299177.html  title=Jay Chou Still Fantasy/How much longer will he dream on?    publisher=East Day  date=2006-09-05   accessdate = 2007-06-02  has been popularized to describe his trademark cross-cultural music and his insistence on singing with relaxed enunciation. Taipei Times once described the meaning of Chou Style: In what has become the archetypal Chou style, Taiwan's favorite son blends pop, rap, blues and a smorgasbord of esthetic elements of world music to create his dream-like never-never landcite web  last = Phipps  first = Gavin  url = http://www.taipeitimes.com/News/feat/archives/2004/08/29/2003200785  title=CD Reviews  publisher=Taipei Times  date=2004-08-29   accessdate = 2007-06-02  He regularly fuses traditional Chinese instruments and styles with R&B or rock to form a new genre called Zhongguo feng zh-tspl t= s= p=Zhnggu fng l=China wind,Ref_label A a none some of which are written in the Pentatonic Scale as opposed to the normal seven-note scale Diatonic scale Diatonic Scale to accentuate an oriental style. Besides his own culture, he also incorporated Flamenco guitar Spanish guitar in Red Imitation zh-tsp t= s= p=hng mfng, American techno music techno/electronic music electronica in Herbalist's Manual zh-tsp t= s= p=Bnco Gngm, rap with subtle classical music undertones in Reverse Scales zh-tsp t= s= p=nln, and Bossa nova Bossanova style in Rosemary zh-cp c= p=mdixing, to name a few. Sound effects from everyday life are frequently weaved into his music, such as bouncing ping pong balls, touch tone phone dialing, helicopter blades, dripping rain, and radio static noise.Ref_label B b none His formal musical training is evident by the use of classical Musical texture textures in his compositions. For example, counterpoint was used in Perfection zh-tsp t= s= p=wnmizhy and Sorry zh-tsp t= s= p=dubuq, while polyphony can be found in The Wound That Ends War zh-tsp t= s= p=zh zhn zh shng and Twilight's Chapter Seven zh-cp c= p=y de d-q zhng.  
Chou's albums have been noted for the lack of change compared to his earlier works, yet he firmly stated that he will not alter his style: They say I've been standing still  but this is the music I want, and I don't see what I want by moving ahead. To demonstrate his point, he named his 2006 album Still Fantasy after his 2001 album Fantasy. His use of relaxed enunciation has been criticized as mumblingzh icon cite news  url = http://www.people.com.cn/GB/yule/1080/2266274.html   title = Jay Chou does not pronounce clearly, resulting in a request for a clearer version of Dragon Fist    date = 2003-12-26   accessdate = 2007-06-02   publisher = people.com.cn   format = News article  which he also insisted will not change;zh icon cite news  url = http://music.ent.tom.com/2007-03-15/0009/10022879.html   title = Vincent Fang discusses music/ Revealed that Jay Chou intentionally enunciates poorly     date = 2007-03-15   accessdate = 2007-06-02   publisher = music.tom.com   format = News article  however, recently he has adopted clearer pronunciation for certain songs, such as Faraway zh-cp c= p=qinl zhwi and Chrysanthemum Terrace zh-tsp t= s= p=jhu ti.zh icon cite web  url = http://news.cnnb.com.cn/system/2006/09/20/005181809.shtml   title = Jay Chou interview/ Being a director gives a greater sense of personal achievement than music     date = 2006-09-20   accessdate = 2007-06-02   publisher = cnnb.com.cn   format = Interview 
Lyrics
Strictly speaking, Chou is more often a singer-composer than a lyricist. Several regulars write the lyrics for most of his music, but the content and style is unified with his own personality and image, covering a diverse range of topics and ideas. Vincent Fang accounts for more than half of the lyrics in his albums, helping to establish an important element in Chou's music: the use of meaningful, imagery- and emotionally-rich lyrics, sometimes written in the form of ancient Chinese poetry with reference to Chinese history or folklore.Ref_label C c none In addition to writing romantic hits,Ref_label D d none he also broaches on war, the Holy Bible Bible, sports, and martial arts.Ref_label E e none Vivian Hsu is a singer herself and has helped with Chou's earlier hits,Ref_label F f none while Huang Jun Lang zh-tsp t= s= p=Hung Jnlng is noted for his work surrounding unusual themes such as a detective story and chess game.Ref_label G g none Chou himself has written lyrics for many love ballads,Ref_label H h none but has also discussed societal ills such as drug addiction in Coward zh-cp c= p=nuf and loss of the rural countryside to urbanization in Terrace fields zh-cp c= p=ttin. Domestic violence discussed in Dad, I am back zh-tsp t=, s=, p=b, w hulai le received a great deal of commotion since he was the first to bring up this taboo subject in Chinese music,cite news  url=http://www.mass-age.com/audio_article.php?id=1230  title=Aiyo, Aiyo, Jay Chou   publisher=www.chinatimes.com, Mass-age   date=2007-02-28   accessdate = 2007-06-02 which helped solidify his status as a pioneer and a unique pop singer capable of approaching serious issues. In the songs Maternal grandmother zh-cp c= p=wip and Listen to your mother zh-tsp t= s= p=tng mma de hu, he voiced his high regard for family values. He addressed personal issues about his failure to enter university in Split zh-cp c= p=fnli, his resentment towards the paparazzi in Besieged From All Sides zh-cp c= p=sminchg, and preached the importance of individuality in Popular Imitation zh-tsp t= s= p=hng mfng.
Collaborations
Chou began as a songwriter for other singers and continued this area of work even after he debuted his own career in singing. He has composed frequently for Jolin Tsai, Landy Wen, and occasionally for other Taiwanese singers such as Coco Lee, S.H.E, Vivian Hsu, Lee-Hom Wang, Will Liu, Valen Hsu, and Hong Kong pop stars Edmond Leung, Gigi Leung, Jordan Chan, Edison Chen, Karen Mok, Leo Ku, Eason Chan, and Joey Yung. He has also written for singers outside of his generationover one dozen songs for his mentor Jacky Wu, later also for Taiwanese singer Jody Chiang zh-cp c= p=Jing Hu, and Hong Kong singers Jacky Cheung, Andy Lau, Lui Fong zh-tsp t= s= p=L Fng, Aaron Kwok, and Kenny Bee.zh icon cite book  last = Chou  first = Jay  title = Grandeur de D Major  format = Book  date = 2004-11-01  publisher = Hua Ren Ban Tu  location = China   isbn = 9572937146   pages = 204211 zh icon cite news  url = http://music.ent.tom.com/2006-12-11/0009/11506235.html   title = Kenny Bee prepares new album/ Jay Chou writes A Ghost's Love Poem     date = 2006-12-11   accessdate = 2007-06-02   publisher = tom.com   format = News article zh icon cite news  url = http://ent.qq.com/a/20070108/000064.htm   title =     date = 2007-01-08   accessdate = 2007-06-02   publisher = ent.qq.com   format = News article zh icon cite news  url = http://enjoy.eastday.com/eastday/enjoy1/e/20070517/u1a2838709.html   title = Jay Chou and Vincent Fang writes song for Joey Yung/King and queen collaborate for the first time     date = 2007-05-17   accessdate = 2007-06-28   publisher = Eastday   format = News article He initiated the band Nan Quan Mama in 2004, selecting band members and overseeing their album production. The group has been noted for sounding too similar to their mentor;zh icon cite news  url = http://www.people.com.cn/BIG5/yule/1085/2535103.html   title =    date = 2004-05-31   accessdate = 2007-06-02   publisher = people.com.cn   format = Review  as a result, Chou has reduced his involvement in t